
The two files are two different input files for the AGB star U Her (uhertot.pos) and the pulsar B1508+55 (B1508+55.pos).

-the .pos file

On the first line a reference positions is given. This is a position of one of the middle observing epochs (ot the average position). Use the same units as the rest of the file.  

From the second line onwards the format is:

For B1508+55.pos: 

1st colummn Modified Julian Date (MJD) at 0.25 accuracy. 
The 2nd and 4th column are the RA and Dec position in seconds (RA) and arcseconds (Dec).
The 3rd and 5th column are the RA and Dec errors (in milliarcseconds).

(The fits are presented in: https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2005ApJ...630L..61C/abstract)

For uhertot.pos:

1st colummn Modified Julian Date (MJD) at 0.25 accuracy. 
The 2nd and 4th column are the RA and Dec position in degrees.
The 3rd and 5th column are the RA and Dec errors also in degrees.
The 6th column when present is not used so should be 0.0.

(These should be the ones used in: https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2007A%26A...472..547V/abstract)



 